          "description": "This is absolutely the worst mom and pop pharmacy that\u2019s supposed to serve the residents which is compromised of a many elderly in Upper East Side/East Harlem. I support small businesses because normally those that do survive the competition of Duane Reade or CVS do right by their community and provide exceptional customer service.\n\nThis pharmacy, Metropolitan Drugs will disappoint and fail at any opportunity to not deliver on even providing subpar level of customer service.\n\nYou get incompetence. In fact, that\u2019s exactly what they strive for every day, how to exhibit to highest and most best level of incompetence.\n\nMy husband spent the whole day trying to get ONE prescription transferred to a CVS because Metropolitan Drugs failed to let us know that they wouldn\u2019t have a frequently prescribed medication ELIQUIS until next week.\n\nNot only did they fail to inform us of the missing prescription, the most incompetent female pharmacy clerk could not transfer ONE prescription medication to CVS so that they can do the job and fill the medicine. Not only did she not do it, she went out of her bestest way to act like the communication was poor, saying things like \u201cI can\u2019t hear you, you\u2019re breaking up.\u201d You get an Oscar for the worst customer service moment delivered to an elderly resident in need.\n\nThank you for making it your priority to prioritize your incompetence instead of doing such a simple task - TRANSFER ONE ELIQUIS PRESCRIPTION to CVS.\n\nCVS wins again. After having to deal with more than one encounter like this, because YES of course this is not the FIRST time this pharmacy has failed us.\n\nMetropolitan Drugs just lost another customer because you royally found a way to be the worst mom and pop pharmacy.",
